text: The Tupolev Tu-124 (NATO code-named Cookpot) is a twin-turbojets airliner built in USSR between 1960 and 1965. It was one of the first civil jet aircraft in the world. It could accommodate between fifty and sixty passengers. 165 examples were built at least. Category:Soviet & Russian aircraft Category:Civil aircraft Category:Tupolev aircraft
title: Tupolev Tu-124
